<subSubSection pageId="91" pageNumber="370" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6760809" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6760809" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6760809/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="370" startId="91.[2015,2187,695,724]" targetBox="[1400,1991,503,917]" targetPageId="91">
<paragraph blockId="91.[2014,2608,498,921]" pageId="91" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2015,2191,695,724]" pageId="91" pageNumber="370">Distribution.</emphasis>
Extreme SE Mexico (Chiapas State) and SC Guatemala.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="91" pageNumber="370" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="91.[2014,2608,498,921]" lastBlockId="91.[1399,2606,926,1472]" pageId="91" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2014,2301,770,803]" pageId="91" pageNumber="370">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 80-124 mm, tail 120-129 mm, ear 15-17 mm, hindfoot 20-25 mm; weight 18-23 g. The Narrow-nosed Harvest Mouse is one of the largest species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1652,1860,926,959]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Reithrodontomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="91" pageNumber="370" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Reithrodontomys</taxonomicName>
. Dorsal pelage is long and dense, ranging from rich orange to a more reddish color. Numerous black guard hairs give the Narrow-nosed Harvest Mouse a dark appearance. Venter is pinkish cinnamon. Eyes have black rings, and ears have a blackish shade. Skull is characterized by long narrow nasal bones, in contrast to other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1790,1998,1083,1116]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Reithrodontomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="91" pageNumber="370" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Reithrodontomys</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="91" pageNumber="370" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="91.[1399,2606,926,1472]" pageId="91" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1401,1512,1123,1156]" pageId="91" pageNumber="370">Habitat.</emphasis>
Wet, temperate habitats, such as evergreen cloud forests, generally at elevations of 2800-2910 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
